<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.2.42" />

<note type="curatorial">3. Hills College Sterling Coll.</note>

<opener>
<dateline><date>July 10, '14</date></dateline>

<salute>Dear Old Man:&#8212;</salute>
</opener>

<p>How's everything with you? Are you reasonably happy? Can you work yet? What do you find worth while doing these hot days?</p>
    
<p>I wrote you some time ago, in reply to Enid's &amp; Sigurd's letter &amp; in acknowledgement of the pretty shells.</p>
    
<p>Drop me a line.</p>
    
<p>How I have been working to have you here, now that my vacation is on! We could tramp over to the Missouri &amp; spend some days &amp; nights in the timber, <del/> and swim together in my river!</p>

<fw type="curatorial">42</fw>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.2.42" />

<p>I hadn't half enough of you, Sterling. Your stay was too short. "Hugh Glass" goes on <unclear>finaly</unclear>. I work three or four hours in the morning &amp; do odd jobs about the place during the rest of the day. 100&#176; in the shade here now! Good luck, Old Man!</p>
<closer>
<salute>Yours always,</salute>
    
<signed>Jno.</signed>
</closer>

</div1>
</body>

